OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781486246
OL,3,C'Giant of the Labour movement' Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies
OL,6,F"Through decades of service, including
OL,7,Fas deputy leader and a minister, he
OL,8,Fnever lost his belief in a more equal
OL,9,FBritain.
OL,11,F"My thoughts are with his wife Maggie
OL,12,Fand his family."
OL,14,FLord Kinnock, who led the party from
OL,15,F1983 to 1992, said: "I am deeply
OL,16,Fsaddened to hear that Roy has died and
OL,17,Fsend my profound sympathy to Maggie.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUtD@PO]wD@UOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781486246
OL,3,C'Giant of the Labour movement' Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies
OL,6,F"Roy was a socialist of deep
OL,7,Fconviction, a dedicated democrat who
OL,8,Fbelieved that liberty should be
OL,9,Funqualified by anything but
OL,10,Fresponsibility and never by background
OL,11,For fortune. He held that freedom had
OL,12,Fto be made real and secure by
OL,13,Fcollective action and contribution, by
OL,14,Faccountability, and by equality.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,306,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F305A1781486246
OL,3,C'Giant of the Labour movement' Roy
OL,4,CHattersley dies
OL,6,F"He was fluent and courageous in
OL,7,Fexpressing these beliefs in speech and
OL,8,Fwriting and wrote countless columns
OL,9,Fand published 20 books. He was never
OL,10,Fsolemn nor deferential and his common
OL,11,Fsense, humour and endless stories made
OL,12,Fhim excellent company.
OL,14,F"All of this made him a valued comrade
OL,15,Fand an incomparable asset to the
OL,16,FLabour Party, to British democracy and
OL,17,Fto wider humanity."
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOUyD@SO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
